President Obama has announced the recipients of the National Medal of Science and the National Medal of Technology and Innovation. These awards are given to scientists, engineers, and inventors who have made outstanding contributions in their fields. The National Medal of Science recognizes individuals who have made significant contributions to science and engineering, while the National Medal of Technology and Innovation recognizes those who have made lasting contributions to America's competitiveness and quality of life. The recipients will receive their awards at a White House ceremony in early 2013.